The police have warned private security companies they should know their place - or face embarrassment and possible arrest. eNCA's Barry Bateman reports. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - You are not the police. This is the warning to private security providers from the SAPS who says that they face arrest if they don’t adhere to the law. READ: Truck attacks: Armed escorts an expensive security option The notice is contained in a police circular issued in December and followed by another issued by the private security regulator this month. But some in the industry are worried that it could curb their ability to support the police. * eNCA’s Barry Bateman reports.